## ROASEQ license summary (non-binding, see AGPL-3.0 above for the actual license)

ROASEQ is licensed under the **GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0)**.

**What this means for you (the user):**
- Use it for free, for any purpose, including commercial
- Self-host it on your own infrastructure, no vendor needed
- Modify the source code to fit your needs
- Distribute your modifications, as long as you publish the source
- Run a hosted service using ROASEQ, **as long as you publish the source of any modifications you make** (this is the AGPL's "network use" clause, which is why we use AGPL over plain GPL)

**What this means for the ROASEQ project:**
- We do not charge for the software itself
- We do offer paid cloud hosting (managed, supported) for teams who don't want to self-host
- The paid cloud tier does not change the AGPL terms for self-hosters; they're independent

For the full legal text, see the body of this file above or visit https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html
